<p><strong>Best investment areas in Hillsborough:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="/cities/brandon/">Brandon</a> / <a href="/cities/valrico/">Valrico</a></strong> — Strong rental demand from families, stable tenant base, reasonable acquisition costs ($300K–$450K for rentable homes). The sweet spot for long-term buy-and-hold investors.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/cities/riverview/">Riverview</a></strong> — Massive rental demand from the growth corridor. New construction can work as rentals but watch for CDD fees eating into cash flow.</li>
<li><strong>Seminole Heights</strong> — Appreciation play more than cash flow. Older homes with character attract young professional tenants willing to pay premium rents.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Pinellas County</h3>
<p><a href="/counties/pinellas/">Pinellas County</a> has high rents but high acquisition costs, compressing cap rates.</p>
